HEADWORD: Photogene
<hw>Pho"to*gene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Photogen</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A photograph.</def>
<mark>[Obsoles.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A more or less continued impression or image on the
